<template>
  <div class="about-page">
    <h2>About AI Sentiment Analyzer</h2>
    
    <div class="content-card">
      <h3>How the Model Works</h3>
      <p>
        Our AI Sentiment Analyzer uses a robust <strong>Logistic Regression</strong> classifier to predict sentiment from textual interactions. 
        When you submit text, the system undergoes a multi-step Natural Language Processing (NLP) pipeline:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Text Cleaning:</strong> Extra spaces, punctuation, and URLs are stripped out. Text is converted to lowercase.</li>
        <li><strong>Tokenization & Vectorization:</strong> The cleaned text is processed using a <code>TF-IDF Vectorizer</code> which turns words into numerical features based on term frequency and inverse document frequency.</li>
        <li><strong>Prediction:</strong> The model evaluates the features and assigns probabilities for each class: Negative, Neutral, and Positive.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="content-card">
      <h3>Dataset Description</h3>
      <p>
        The model is trained on a substantial corpus labeled <code>sentiment_data.csv</code>. 
        The dataset details:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Size:</strong> Approximately 241,000 text comments.</li>
        <li><strong>Structure:</strong> Columns include <code>index</code>, <code>comment</code>, and <code>sentiment</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Labels:</strong> 0 (Negative), 1 (Neutral), 2 (Positive).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="content-card">
      <h3>Model Performance Metrics</h3>
      <p>
        The dataset is split 80/20 for training and testing. Based on current evaluations:
      </p>
      <div class="metric-tags">
        <span class="tag">High Accuracy</span>
        <span class="tag">Lightweight Engine</span>
        <span class="tag">FastAPI Backend</span>
        <span class="tag">Real-time Inference</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

